Call for Papers
Papers are being solicited in all areas of interest in engineering and engineering technology education .
Topics of interest include :
* Criteria 2000 * Assessment tools * Design in the curriculum * Partnering with industry * Active / Cooperative learning
* Tutoring and preparing students * Design and retenetion * Assessing internet effectiveness * Portfolios and surveys
Submit a 200 word abstract of the paper to be considered for presentation at this meeting . The paper should not have been published previously . The abstract should contain the title of the paper , the name of the authors , their affiliation , mailing address , telephone numbers , and e-mail address ( if available ) .
The deadline for abstracts is April 21 .
Abstracts may be submitted by email , however , the sender should be alert to receiving an email acknowledgement within three working days . If this acknowledgement is not forthcoming , it would be advisable to use email or telephone to confirm receipt of the abstract .
Send email abstracts to nrmalik @ icaen . uiowa . edu .
Decisions will be made by May 16 , 1997 , and the contact person will be notified soon after that date . Manuscripts of selected papers should be received by August 27 , 1997 . The selected papers will be published in the proceedings of the Conference .
Based on a regional engineering faculty survey , we are planning to include half-day workshops and invited lectures as a part of the conference . If you are interested in a particular workshop topic or would like to nominate someone as an invited lecturer , contact your campus representative or the conference organizers via mail , phone , fax , or e-mail ( see below ) . Your input is important to ensure a high quality conference .
